President Donald Trump has announced his intent to nominate Peter A. Feldman as a Commissioner of the Consumer Product Safety Commission for the remainder of a seven-year term expiring on October 16, 2019. Feldman is currently senior counsel to the United States Senate Committee on Commerce, Science, and Transportation, where he advises on consumer protection, product safety, data, and privacy issues. He has been involved in the development and enactment of major consumer protection legislation and has worked on congressional oversight of federal agencies, including the Consumer Product Safety Commission. Feldman has a B.A. from Colgate University and a J.D. from American University's Washington College of Law.